"In private conversations, though, he has sometimes said that it's not really Ulman's actions that he is sympathetic to," says Strang.
Lived a peaceful life, there is no suspicion of lawlessness or corruption.
How is Zemgala remembered today?
It is a pity, but for a large part he associates himself only with a street in Riga.
