The specialist encourages a small conversation about these such natural and human feelings - the anger and rage that everyone periodically experiences.
Aggression - this is already a physical act addressed to another person, and it usually appears when we feel angry.
When we adults are angry, upset - we usually know what is happening to us and how to deal with it.
We can express our anger and rage in ourselves: express, suppress, hide, keep in ourselves, tell our friends or other loved ones about it, we can kick the couch in anger, smoke a cigarette (this is not the best way to dispel anger!), take a shower, hit a kulak around the table and do other things that we don't usually do.
