Children, when they experience anger, do not understand what is happening to them, how to name it and how to live with it.
They can say: "Go away!", You are a fool", "Bad mom", "I don't see you", "I will not be friends with you" - and very rarely when they are able to say: "I am angry with you".
Children live in the literal sense, they are completely right here, at this moment, they are spontaneous and sincere in the expression of their feelings, and often also find themselves captive to various emotions.
It is very important that parents do not forbid the child to show feelings, including anger, do not be ashamed of it and do not show up, but, on the contrary, help the child.
