The Latvian National Museum of Art pays tribute to the painter Janis Rozentāls (1866-1916) with an extensive retrospective in the newly opened Great Exhibition Hall, whose one hundred and fiftieth birthday is included in the UNESCO calendar of celebrated days internationally.
The retrospective exhibition, which features more than 150 works, is one of the central events of the Janis Rozentals anniversary year program.
The selection of artworks is mostly made from the collection of the Latvian National Museum of Art, which convincingly represents the main stages and genres of the classic's creative activity, stylistic variability and variety of techniques.
