In the Indian capital, a man dying on the side of the road is robbed.
In the Indian capital, no one has seemed to know about a man dying on the side of the road - it turns out he slept for an hour on the side of the road and then still robbed, according to the BBC.
The man, identified as Mattiboul, was reported to have ridden a rickshaw by day and worked as a security guard at night.
Matiboul was heading home on the road at 5:30 a.m. when he was hit by a car.
Surveillance camera footage shows the driver got out of the car to look at the victim and then drove away.
An hour later, when no one seemed to know about the bleeding man, he was robbed by a garnish.
About 90 minutes after being hit, police arrived at the scene and the victim was taken to hospital, where he died from his injuries.
