The future of the Portland smelter is becoming uncertain as an ambitious contract is terminated.
The future of the aluminum smelter and hundreds of its employees in Portland, Victoria has become uncertain as its main customer, the energy company, has announced the termination of cooperation.
This statement is based on the Victorian government's plans to end subsidizing the energy company, which is vital for the company to continue its work.
The 20-year subsidies will end in November.
