Latvenergo follows the process of opening the gas market also from the position of a potential trader.
The state energy company Latvenergo follows the process of opening the gas market from the position of both a consumer and a potential trader, said Ivita Bidere, the company's press secretary.
"The decision on whether latvenergo will also join the gas market as a trader in the future will be determined by what gas market model and regulatory framework will be created."
"For our part, we are actively involved in drafting and commenting on legislation and submitting our proposals," Bidere said.
Agency BNS already wrote that the Ministry of Economics (EM) in cooperation with the Public Utilities Commission and the energy company "Latvijas Gāze" has developed draft Cabinet regulations "Regulations for the Trade and Use of Natural Gas" that will change the existing principles of operation of the natural gas market, ensuring the right of natural gas users to freely choose a natural gas trader from April 3, 2017.
While working on the new regulation of the natural gas market, EM aims to make the natural gas trading process as simple and understandable as possible.
Therefore, the "merchant-centric model" has been chosen as the most efficient and user-friendly service solution, in which all activities related to customer service are provided by the trader - one contract, one invoice and one place of provision of information and customer service, leaving to the discretion of the distribution system operator the technical issues of the natural gas distribution system.
A similar solution is currently being implemented in electricity trading.
We remind you that gradual opening of the market is planned for household customers - even after April 3, 2017, those household customers who do not want to choose another natural gas trader will be able to continue receiving natural gas from the existing trader at a regulated price, thus becoming related customers.
"In such a case, the obligation to supply natural gas to related customers at a regulated price is imposed on the public trader", the ministry informed.
In turn, merchants will have to choose a natural gas trader with whom to enter into a natural gas trade contract.
Until entering into a natural gas trade contract, trade in natural gas for a specific period of time shall be ensured to merchants by the previous natural gas trader for the price specified thereby.
The draft Cabinet regulations specify in detail the rights and obligations of the natural gas trader, system operator and users.
This Regulation prescribes the procedures by which natural gas shall be supplied to customers and the supply thereof shall be discontinued, the requirements for safe use of the natural gas system, the rights and obligations of the trader, public trader, system operator, user, and owner of the gasified object in the supply and use of natural gas; the procedures for making settlements for the services received, the amount of late payment interest, the procedures for changing traders and supplying customers in the event of disruptions in the supply of natural gas; the procedures by which the supply of natural gas to related customers shall be ensured by a public trader.
