It has already been announced that in the restoration of the cultural and historical park on an area of more than 42 hectares, the restoration of access roads and street sections, the construction of an interactive nature tourism object, landscaping of the territory and the construction of parking lots on Emīla Darzina Street, which will contribute to the socio-economic development of the city of Jurmala and the increase in the number of tourists, Jurmala City Council plans to attract 14.5 million euros from the resources of the European Union funds, co-financing with three to four million euros.
